","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the gutter needs more space (when the number of digits in the numbers increases eg. adding a line after line 99),"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it will notify it’s delegate via the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GutterViewDelegate\/gutterViewWidthDidUpdate(newWidth:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method. In"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"SourceEditor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", this notifies the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/TextViewController","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", which in turn updates the textview’s edge insets","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to adjust for the new leading inset."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This view also listens for selection updates, and draws a selected background on selected lines to keep the illusion"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that the gutter’s line numbers are inline with the line itself."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The gutter view has insets of it’s own that are relative to the widest line index. By default, these insets are 20px","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"leading, and 12px trailing. However, this view also has a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GutterView\/backgroundEdgeInsets"},{"type":"text","text":" property, that pads"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the rect that has a background drawn. This allows the text to be scrolled under the gutter view for 8px before being","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlapped by the gutter. It should help the textview keep the cursor visible if the user types while the cursor is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"off the leading edge of the editor.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"me